<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2><span style="font-size:16pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Relevance of Gandhi Today&nbsp;</span></span></h2>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal">
<h4><a href="https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/a-lesson-in-swaraj-from-informal-women-workers/story-9FPfjQex0Nr0fX10ldSScM.html" style="text-decoration:none"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><u>Swaraj</u></span></span></a></h4>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Inspired by</span></span><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><em> Swaraj</em></span></span><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">, women cooperatives have been significantly contributing to GDP. e.g. SEWA These women show how to transcend caste and community barriers in achieving </span></span><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><em><u>self-reliance.</u></em></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Possible only by removing untouchability, Hindu-Muslim Unity, swadeshi goods, </span></span><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><strong><em>decentralised employment</em></strong></span></span><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">, and freedom from fear. Women extended this idea to include gender discrimination.</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Swaraj is about freedom from hunger and poverty.</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Outer and inner swaraj as foundations of moral society. Inner swaraj : ruling over emotions like greed, anger, jealousy</span></span></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal">
<h4><a href="https://epaper.hindustantimes.com/Home/ShareArticle?OrgId=2fe399f4" style="text-decoration:none"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><u>Constructive work</u></span></span></a><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"> for the community</span></span></h4>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Besides </span></span><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><strong><em>political freedom</em></strong></span></span><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">, he simultaneously focussed on </span></span><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><strong><em>social</em></strong></span></span><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"> and </span></span><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><strong><em>economic</em></strong></span></span><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"> problems of the country. Mere transfer of power without social harmony and employment would mean very little.&nbsp;</span></span>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-roman"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Similar idea of Bose : Social and political revolution at same time</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-roman"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Nehru too focused on Economic Plan and social rights (voting etc)</span></span></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Economic manufacturing : not efficient but based on impact upon human lives.&nbsp;</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">All India village industries association, 1930s : For boosting rural economy by leather processing, jaggery from palms instead of sugarcane, handmade paper.</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Talisman :&nbsp;</span></span></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal">
<h4><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Education</span></span></h4>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">No divorce between labor and intelligence. Work by hand. : relevant today unemployable graduates</span></span></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal">
<h4><a href="https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/gandhi-s-four-visits-to-assam/story-vy5ihuftNmSAh79eBwmf6L.html" style="text-decoration:none"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><u>Incidence of boosting morale of local people</u></span></span></a><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"> : Leadership</span></span></h4>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Along with eminent Assamese public figures, including Nabin Chandra Bardoloi and Tarunram Phukan, (1921, post NCM) Gandhi ji lit a small heap and asked crowd to throw foreign clothes in the heap.</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">1909, Hind Swaraj : Gandhi had mentioned Assamese as barbarous. 1921, Gandhi now offered a public apology for being a poor student of history and for being so little read about the region.</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">NCM turned violent: Gandhiji took public responsibility and called it a Himalayan Blunder.</span></span></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal">
<h4><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Trusteeship</span></span></h4>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Based on Aparigraha (no owning), asetya (no stealing from earth or future generations) : Morality having precedence over Economy</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><em><u>Attitude cultivation</u></em></span></span><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"> of trustee : i.e. If you have more than your needs, you become trustee of excess for God’s people (aka </span></span><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><strong><em>Daridanarayan</em></strong></span></span><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">) : redistributive justice&nbsp;</span></span></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal">
<h4><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Gandhi on Attitude change :&nbsp;</span></span></h4>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Oppression : victims were complicit in their oppression and needed to rebel against themselves</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Trusteeship : Aparigraha : ethics based economy</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Courage for Gandhi, was bound with self-respect. Self-respect must be invoked to generate courage against injustice. That is the way for fearlessness.</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Let noble thoughts come from all directions.&nbsp;</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">On Consumerist Culture: Call for conscience based consumption. Focussing on internally satisfying lifestyle.</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Obama : “He embodies the kind of transformational change that can be made when ordinary people come together to do extraordinary things."</span></span></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal">
<h4><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">In extremist times :&nbsp;</span></span></h4>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Hindu Muslim Unity : Indian celebrating freedom, Gandhiji bringing peace to riot-hit areas.</span></span></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">International</span></span>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Portugal setup gandhi prize</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha">&nbsp;</li></ol></li></ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3><span style="font-size:13.999999999999998pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Satyagraha&nbsp;</span></span></h3>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal">
<h4><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">The Principle:&nbsp;</span></span></h4>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Assumption : goodness of human conduct&nbsp;</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Love for truth =&gt; compassion for oppressor</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">First convince oneself of the truth</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Begin with self purification =&gt; fasting as indispendable ritual during potests.</span></span></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal">
<h4><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Application of satyagraha</span></span></h4>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Constructive programme : Reform must begin from within</span></span>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-roman"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Eliminate evils : Against untouchability and social evils</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-roman"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Empower oneself and society : Trusteeship model, Schools for all sections,&nbsp;</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-roman"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Helped develop inclusive model of swaraj.</span></span></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Persuasion&nbsp;</span></span>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-roman"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Pamphlet,&nbsp;</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-roman"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">7 sins published in Young India in 1925</span></span></li></ol></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal">
<h4><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Ahimsa and satyagraha : Indispensable duo&nbsp;</span></span></h4>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">AHimsa : Means, satyagraha is end</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Ahimsa : Essential to find truth (=satyagraha). The suffering during search for truth should not lead to violence&nbsp;</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">No violence in thoughts (=no ill will )&nbsp; =&gt; compassion for the evil doer,&nbsp;</span></span></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal">
<h4><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">As a tool for social change&nbsp;</span></span></h4>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Satyagraha to be used for the oteher, not personal gains&nbsp;</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Aim is to reform the oppressor not defeat, embarras him, neither punish,</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">It demands voluntary change in all parties to conflict.&nbsp;</span></span></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal">
<h4><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Lessons from South africa</span></span></h4>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Not for the weak. Brave moral act.&nbsp;</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Demands love for the truth to endure suffering. E.g. beaten during public burning of certificates</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha">&nbsp;</li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal">
<h4><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Criticism</span></span></h4>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Violence&nbsp;</span></span>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-roman"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">during 1942 QIM&nbsp;</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-roman"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Satyagraha did not work as effectively in Princely States as in rest of India because British protection to State Rulers allowed them to withstand popular pressure. {Shekhar Bandopadhyay}</span></span></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Moral support to british during WWI&nbsp;</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Hindu muslim riots during partition could not be assuaged</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Assumed goodness of human nature =&gt; fails to recognise frailities of human nature.&nbsp;</span></span></li></ol></li></ol>
<h4><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Conclusion</span></span></h4>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Thus ideas of gandhiji remain</span></span><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"> </span></span><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"> unfinished business and continue to guide our way to </span></span><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><em>doosri ajadi </em></span></span><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">from hunger and poverty towards swaraj.</span></span></p>
